The paper deals with algorithms and probability spaces, which are common topics in computer science. The Lovasz Local Lemma is a well-known probabilistic tool used in many areas of computer science, including algorithms, complexity theory, and discrete mathematics. The paper also mentions resampling oracles, which are used in randomized algorithms and have connections to information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
